# Notification banner

Use the shared **in-app banner** system for budget alerts, summaries, and reminders.  
These are **not** OS push notifications (no `Notification.requestPermission` yet).

## Components

| Piece | Path |
|-------|------|
| UI | `src/app/components/ui/NotificationBanner.tsx` |
| Provider | `src/app/context/NotificationContext.tsx` |
| Host (in mockup) | `NotificationBannerHost` in `DeviceShell.tsx` |
| Rules engine | `src/app/services/notificationAlerts.ts` |
| Auto runner | `src/app/components/NotificationAlertRunner.tsx` (main app only) |

## Showing a banner

Always go through the provider ‚Äî never mount `NotificationBanner` ad hoc in screens.

```tsx
import { useNotifications } from '../context/NotificationContext';

const { showNotification } = useNotifications();

showNotification({
  id: 'unique-dedupe-key',      // required ‚Äî used for queue + localStorage dedupe
  title: 'Approaching budget limit',
  message: '82% of your monthly budget is used.',
  variant: 'warning',             // 'info' | 'warning' | 'success'
});
```

Provider is mounted in `routes.tsx` ‚Üí `NotificationProvider` (wraps the app tree).

## Banner behaviour (required)

- **Enter**: slide from above (`translateY(-100%)` ‚Üí `0`), ~320ms ease-out.
- **Duration**: auto-dismiss after **5 seconds** (`NOTIFICATION_BANNER_DURATION_MS`).
- **Dismiss**: **X** button calls `onDismiss` immediately (plays exit animation).
- **Position**: inside `DeviceShell` ‚Üí `device-shell__content`, **flush top**, **edge-to-edge** (no horizontal inset, no card radius, bottom border only). `z-index: 280`.
- **Queue**: one visible at a time; auto-runner shows **at most one** alert per evaluation. Manual `showNotification` replaces any pending queue entry (no long FIFO chains).

## User preferences

Stored on `AppState.notificationPreferences`:

- `budgetAlerts` ‚Äî monthly + category budget thresholds
- `weeklySummary` ‚Äî once per calendar week
- `billReminders` ‚Äî recurring charges due within 3 days
- `goalMilestones` ‚Äî 50% / 75% / 100% of category goals
- `recurringReminders` ‚Äî synced with bill reminders for cloud DB

Toggles: onboarding **Stay on track** + **Settings ‚Üí Notifications**.  
Updates use `dispatch({ type: 'SET_NOTIFICATION_PREFERENCES', preferences })`.

## Alert flows (when banners fire)

Mount `NotificationAlertRunner` only under the main app shell (`RootLayout`), not during onboarding.

`evaluateNotificationAlerts()` returns **one** payload: the highest-priority unseen alert. Lower-priority candidates are skipped until the user dismisses the current one and state changes.

| Priority (high ‚Üí low) | Toggle | Trigger | Dedupe id |
|----------------------|--------|---------|-----------|
| 1 | Budget alerts | Month spend ‚â• 100% | `{YYYY-MM}-budget-over` |
| 2 | Budget alerts | Any category ‚â• 100% (worst wins) | `{YYYY-MM}-cat-{id}-over` |
| 3 | Budget alerts | Month spend ‚â• 80% | `{YYYY-MM}-budget-warning` |
| 4 | Budget alerts | Category ‚â• 80% | `{YYYY-MM}-cat-{id}-warn` |
| 5 | Bill reminders | Soonest recurring due in 0‚Äì3 days | `{YYYY-MM}-bill-{seriesKey}` |
| 6 | Goal milestones | Highest band only: 50% or 75% (not if ‚â•80%; no 50+75+100 stack) | `{YYYY-MM}-milestone-{id}-{pct}` |
| 7 | Weekly summary | Week with spend > 0 | `{weekStart}-weekly-summary` |

Seen ids persist in `localStorage` key `spendr:notification-seen:v1` (30-day TTL).  
Call `markNotificationSeen(id)` on dismiss (provider does this automatically). Superseded milestone ids are marked seen when a higher band or category over/warn applies.

## Do not

- Use inline absolute ‚Äútoast‚Äù divs for product alerts (export toasts in Settings are legacy; prefer `showNotification` for new work).
- Fire the same `id` twice in one session (provider dedupes active + queue).
- Mount `NotificationAlertRunner` on onboarding or auth routes.
- Add emoji to banner copy.
- Use non-Phosphor icons in banner chrome (X button uses Phosphor `X`).

## Adding a new alert type

1. Add a preference flag if it should be toggleable.
2. Add a scored candidate in `evaluateNotificationAlerts()` with a **stable unique `id`** and `priority`.
3. Respect `prefs` and `wasNotificationSeen(id)`; keep priorities documented in the table above.
4. Document the row in this file‚Äôs table.

